  <tr class="bad-row"><td>25</td><td>Roga</td><td>NW Corner</td><td>❌ Inauspicious</td><td>Avoid entrances</td></tr>
  <tr><td>26</td><td>Naga</td><td>North</td><td>○ Neutral</td><td>Water tank</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>27</td><td>Mukhya</td><td>North</td><td>★★ Best</td><td>Main entrance (N road)</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>28</td><td>Bhallata</td><td>North</td><td>★★ Best</td><td>Main entrance (N road)</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>29</td><td>Soma</td><td>North</td><td>★ Good</td><td>Main entrance, water</td></tr>
  <tr><td>30</td><td>Bhujanga</td><td>North</td><td>○ Neutral</td><td>Garden</td></tr>
  <tr><td>31</td><td>Aditi</td><td>North</td><td>○ Neutral</td><td>Open space</td></tr>
  <tr><td>32</td><td>Diti</td><td>North</td><td>○ Neutral</td><td>Store</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- CHAPTER 8 -->
<h1 class="chapter" id="ch8">Chapter 8: 16 Zones and Life Aspects</h1>
<p>The 16 directions (N, NNE, NE, ENE, E, ESE, SE, SSE, S, SSW, SW, WSW, W, WNW, NW, NNW) each govern a specific area of life. Understanding these helps architects place rooms to maximise positive life outcomes for the occupants.</p>
<table>
  <tr><th>Zone</th><th>Direction</th><th>Life Aspect</th><th>Best Rooms</th></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>NE</td><td>North-East</td><td>Personality & Health</td><td>Puja Room, Open Space</td></tr>
  <tr><td>ENE</td><td>East-North-East</td><td>Luck & Spirituality</td><td>Study, Meditation</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>E</td><td>East</td><td>Immunity & Creativity</td><td>Bathroom, Children's Room</td></tr>
  <tr><td>ESE</td><td>East-South-East</td><td>Mental Peace & Education</td><td>Study Room</td></tr>
  <tr class="bad-row"><td>SE</td><td>South-East</td><td>Fire & Energy</td><td>Kitchen only</td></tr>
  <tr><td>SSE</td><td>South-South-East</td><td>Finance & Family Status</td><td>Locker, Safe</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>S</td><td>South</td><td>Fame & Recognition</td><td>Bedroom 2, Dining</td></tr>
  <tr><td>SSW</td><td>South-South-West</td><td>Disposal & Release</td><td>Toilet, Waste</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>SW</td><td>South-West</td><td>Stability & Relationships</td><td>Master Bedroom</td></tr>
  <tr><td>WSW</td><td>West-South-West</td><td>Profit & Success</td><td>Study, Home Office</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>W</td><td>West</td><td>Gains & Contentment</td><td>Dining, Children</td></tr>
  <tr><td>WNW</td><td>West-North-West</td><td>Rest & Recovery</td><td>Guest Room</td></tr>
  <tr><td>NW</td><td>North-West</td><td>Support & Networking</td><td>Toilet, Guest, Store</td></tr>
  <tr><td>NNW</td><td>North-North-West</td><td>Attraction & Relationships</td><td>Bedroom, Living</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>N</td><td>North</td><td>Prosperity & Reputation</td><td>Hall, Living Room</td></tr>
  <tr><td>NNE</td><td>North-North-East</td><td>Challenges & Growth</td><td>Open space, Garden</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- CHAPTER 9 -->
<h1 class="chapter" id="ch9">Chapter 9: Marma Sthanas — Sacred Points</h1>
<div class="warn">
  <strong>⚠️ Critical Construction Rule:</strong> Marma Sthanas are the vital joints of the Vastu Purusha — equivalent to the vital points (marmas) of the human body. No column, beam joint, well, septic tank, staircase newel post, or heavy structural element should be placed at a Marma Sthana. Violation causes structural and health problems.
</div>
<p>The primary Marma Sthanas in the 9×9 grid are located at the intersections of the 3rd and 6th Pada lines — creating 8 points around the Brahma Sthana, plus the 4 corner intersections.</p>
<div class="highlight">
  In Samartha Vastu software, Marma Sthanas are shown as red dots on the canvas. These update automatically based on your built area dimensions and True North rotation.
</div>

<!-- ═══════════ PART C — PRACTICAL APPLICATION ═══════════ -->
<h1 class="chapter" id="part-c">PART C — PRACTICAL APPLICATION</h1>

<!-- CHAPTER 10 -->
<h1 class="chapter" id="ch10">Chapter 10: Site Selection Rules</h1>
<h2 class="section">Plot Shape</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Shape</th><th>Rating</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>Perfect Square</td><td>★★ Excellent</td><td>Equal energy on all sides</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>Rectangle (L&gt;W by max 1:2)</td><td>★ Good</td><td>Most common — works well</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Rectangle (L&gt;W more than 1:2)</td><td>○ Acceptable</td><td>Proportional Padavinyasa handles this</td></tr>
  <tr class="bad-row"><td>Triangular</td><td>❌ Avoid</td><td>Cuts create energy imbalance</td></tr>
  <tr class="bad-row"><td>Irregular (random sides)</td><td>❌ Difficult</td><td>Requires expert Vastu correction</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>North-East extension</td><td>★★ Excellent</td><td>Extends the most auspicious corner</td></tr>
  <tr class="bad-row"><td>South-West extension</td><td>❌ Avoid</td><td>Extends inauspicious Pitra corner</td></tr>
  <tr class="bad-row"><td>North-East cut</td><td>❌ Avoid</td><td>Cuts the most auspicious corner</td></tr>
</table>

<h2 class="section">Road Direction Rules</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>Road Facing</th><th>Rating</th><th>Best Entrance Devatha</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>East</td><td>★★ Excellent</td><td>Jayanta (3rd), Mahendra (4th)</td><td>Morning sun — health and growth</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>North</td><td>★★ Excellent</td><td>Mukhya (27th), Bhallata (28th)</td><td>Prosperity direction</td></tr>
  <tr><td>South</td><td>★ Good with care</td><td>Vitatha (11th), Gruhakshat (12th)</td><td>Requires correct Devatha placement</td></tr>
  <tr><td>West</td><td>★ Good with care</td><td>Sugriva (19th), Pushpadanta (20th)</td><td>Acceptable with correct planning</td></tr>
</table>

