<!-- CHAPTER 12 -->
<h1 class="chapter" id="ch12">Chapter 12: Main Entrance — Dwara Selection</h1>
<p>The main entrance (Dwara) is the most critical element of Vastu planning. It must be placed on an <strong>auspicious Devatha</strong> position. The best Devathas vary based on which direction the road faces.</p>
<table>
  <tr><th>Road Direction</th><th>★★ Best Devathas</th><th>★ Acceptable</th><th>❌ Avoid</th></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>East Road</td><td>Jayanta (3rd), Mahendra (4th)</td><td>Parjanya (2nd), Surya (5th)</td><td>Shikhi corner</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>South Road</td><td>Vitatha (11th), Gruhakshat (12th)</td><td>Pusha (10th), Yama (13th)</td><td>Agni corner</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>West Road</td><td>Sugriva (19th), Pushpadanta (20th)</td><td>Varuna (21st), Dauvarika (18th)</td><td>Pitra corner</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>North Road</td><td>Mukhya (27th), Bhallata (28th)</td><td>Soma (29th), Naga (26th)</td><td>Roga corner</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="highlight">
  <strong>In Samartha Vastu:</strong> Click any Devatha label on the canvas to set that Devatha as your main entrance. The software shows ★ Good and ✗ Bad ratings for all 32 positions. The AUTO GATE button automatically places the entrance on the best auspicious Devatha for your road direction.
</div>

<!-- CHAPTER 13 -->
<h1 class="chapter" id="ch13">Chapter 13: Ayadi Shastra — Navavargulu</h1>
<p>Ayadi Shastra is the mathematical system of calculating 9 astrological parameters (Navavargulu) from the house dimensions. These parameters determine the compatibility of the house with its occupants.</p>
<h2 class="section">The 9 Parameters (Navavargulu)</h2>
<table>
  <tr><th>#</th><th>Parameter</th><th>Auspicious Values</th><th>Calculation</th></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>1</td><td>Ayam (Yoni)</td><td>Dhwaja(1)★★, Simha(3)★, Vrusha(5)★, Gaja(7)★</td><td>Based on EW dimension</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2</td><td>Aaya (Income)</td><td>Must exceed Runam (debt)</td><td>Formula from Viswakarma text</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3</td><td>Runam (Debt)</td><td>Must be less than Aaya</td><td>Formula from Viswakarma text</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4</td><td>Nakshatra (Star)</td><td>Should match owner's birth star</td><td>27 Nakshatras cycle</td></tr>
  <tr><td>5</td><td>Tithi</td><td>Avoid 4, 8, 14, Amavasya</td><td>Lunar day calculation</td></tr>
  <tr><td>6</td><td>Varam (Day)</td><td>Wednesday, Thursday, Friday best</td><td>Day of week calculation</td></tr>
  <tr><td>7</td><td>Yoga</td><td>Siddha, Amrita, Shubha</td><td>Sun+Moon position</td></tr>
  <tr><td>8</td><td>Karana</td><td>Fixed Karanas preferred</td><td>Half-tithi calculation</td></tr>
  <tr class="good-row"><td>9</td><td>Ayusham (Age)</td><td>Higher value = longer-lasting house</td><td>Based on NS dimension</td></tr>
</table>
<div class="good">
  <strong>Yoni (Ayam) — Most Important:</strong> Dhwaja Yoni (1) is the most auspicious — represents a flag flying high. Simha (3) = lion, strength. Vrusha (5) = bull, stability. Gaja (7) = elephant, prosperity. Use the Dhwaja/Simha/Vrusha/Gaja buttons in Samartha Vastu to find dimensions that give auspicious Yoni values.
</div>

<!-- CHAPTER 14 -->
<h1 class="chapter" id="ch14">Chapter 14: G+1 Floor Planning</h1>
<p>Samartha Vastu supports complete Ground Floor + First Floor (G+1) planning. Each floor has its own independent Padavinyasa calculation.</p>
<div class="grid2">
  <div class="card">
    <h4>🏠 Ground Floor (GF)</h4>
    <p>Default view when app opens</p>
    <p>Contains all main living areas</p>
    <p>Separate room list, walls, labels</p>
    <p>Independent Devatha calculations</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h4>🏢 First Floor (1F)</h4>
    <p>Click 1F tab to switch</p>
    <p>GF rooms copied as template on first visit</p>
    <p>Modify independently from GF</p>
    <p>Printed separately in PDF report</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="highlight">
  <strong>Staircase Rule:</strong> Place the staircase in the same position on both GF and 1F. The staircase should be in the SW or S zone — never in the NE or centre Brahma Sthana.
</div>

<!-- ═══════════ PART D — CONSTRUCTION GUIDANCE ═══════════ -->
<h1 class="chapter" id="part-d">PART D — CONSTRUCTION GUIDANCE</h1>

<!-- CHAPTER 15 -->
<h1 class="chapter" id="ch15">Chapter 15: 19-Step Planning Process</h1>
<p>Viswakarma Vastu planning follows a precise sequence of steps — from the first site measurement to handing over the completed building. These steps ensure that every Vastu principle is applied correctly at every stage of construction.</p>
<table>
  <tr><th>#</th><th>Step</th><th>Vastu Purpose</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1</td><td>Land boundary drawing with measurements</td><td>Establishes exact plot dimensions for Padavinyasa</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2</td><td>True North determination via satellite/Google Maps</td><td>Accurate astronomical direction — not magnetic compass</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3</td><td>Ayadi calculation for proposed dimensions</td><td>Ensures Yoni, Aaya, Runam are auspicious</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4</td><td>Vastu Purush Mandala casting with Marma points</td><td>Identifies all Marma Sthanas before structural design</td></tr>
  <tr><td>5</td><td>Client requirements — bedrooms, toilets, kitchen</td><td>Maps functional needs to Vastu zones</td></tr>
  <tr><td>6</td><td>Main door (Dwara) position fixing</td><td>Places entrance on most auspicious Devatha</td></tr>
  <tr><td>7</td><td>Initial sample drawing preparation</td><td>First Vastu layout for client review</td></tr>
  <tr><td>8</td><td>Client discussion and modifications (5–6 rounds)</td><td>Balances Vastu rules with practical requirements</td></tr>
  <tr><td>9</td><td>First floor plan preparation</td><td>Applies same Padavinyasa to upper floor</td></tr>
  <tr><td>10</td><td>Column placement as per Marma Sthana</td><td>Structural columns avoid all Marma Sthanas</td></tr>
  <tr><td>11</td><td>Foundation layout preparation</td><td>Foundation grid aligned with Pada grid</td></tr>
  <tr><td>12</td><td>Structural drawings</td><td>All structural elements verified against Vastu grid</td></tr>
  <tr><td>13</td><td>Interior and furniture placement as per Vastu</td><td>Furniture placed per zone rules</td></tr>
  <tr><td>14</td><td>Internal wall colours by zone</td><td>Zone-appropriate colours enhance Vastu energy</td></tr>
  <tr><td>15</td><td>Vastu correction (if required)</td><td>Remedies for any unavoidable violations</td></tr>
  <tr><td>16</td><td>Foundation ritual guidance (Bhoomi Puja)</td><td>Auspicious Muhurtha for breaking ground</td></tr>
  <tr><td>17</td><td>Construction stage support</td><td>On-site verification at key stages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>18</td><td>Griha Pravesh preparation</td><td>Auspicious housewarming ceremony timing</td></tr>
  <tr><td>19</td><td>Post-occupancy follow-up</td><td>Verify all Vastu elements properly implemented</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- CHAPTER 16 -->
<h1 class="chapter" id="ch16">Chapter 16: Muhurtha Basics</h1>
<p>Muhurtha is the selection of an auspicious time for beginning important activities. In Vastu construction, Muhurtha is required for:</p>
<div class="grid2">
  <div class="card">
    <h4>🌍 Bhoomi Puja</h4>
    <p>Foundation laying ceremony</p>
    <p>Best Nakshatras: Rohini, Mrigashira, Uttara Phalguni, Hasta, Chitra, Swati, Anuradha</p>
    <p>Avoid: Ardra, Ashlesha, Jyeshtha, Moola</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h4>🏠 Griha Pravesh</h4>
    <p>Housewarming ceremony</p>
    <p>Best Nakshatras: Rohini, Uttara, Hasta, Swati, Revati, Uttarashada</p>
    <p>Best Tithis: 2, 3, 5, 7, 10, 11, 13</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h4>🔨 First Column</h4>
    <p>Placing the foundation column</p>
    <p>Must avoid all Marma Sthana positions</p>
    <p>Best done on Monday, Wednesday, Thursday</p>
  </div>
  <div class="card">
    <h4>🚪 Door Frame</h4>
    <p>Fixing the main door frame</p>
    <p>Best on Thursday (Bruhaspativara)</p>
    <p>Avoid Saturday and Sunday</p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="highlight blue">
  <strong>Note:</strong> A complete Muhurtha guide based on Viswakarma Prakashika is available as a separate reference document from Samartha Vastu.
</div>

<!-- CHAPTER 17 -->
<h1 class="chapter" id="ch17">Chapter 17: Vastu Do's and Don'ts</h1>
<h2 class="section" id="dos-donts">20 Essential Vastu Rules for Every Client</h2>
<div class="good">
  <strong>✅ DO's:</strong>
  <ol style="padding-left:18px;margin-top:8px;color:#4ade80;font-size:0.88rem;">
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Always enter True North degrees first — it shifts all 32 Devatha positions correctly</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Place Master Bedroom in SW — the most stable, grounded zone</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Place Puja Room in NE — the most sacred, pure zone</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Place Kitchen in SE — fire element matches Agni zone energy</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Keep Brahma Sthana (centre) open — no columns, no heavy load</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Select main entrance on auspicious Devatha (★ Good or ★★ Best)</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Place Borewell in NE compound wall corner</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Place Septic Tank in NW or SSW zone</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Place Staircase in SW or S zone</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Achieve Vastu Health Score of 75%+ before finalising the plan</li>
  </ol>
</div>
<div class="warn" style="margin-top:16px;">
  <strong>❌ DON'Ts:</strong>
  <ol style="padding-left:18px;margin-top:8px;color:#f87171;font-size:0.88rem;">
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Never place an entrance on corner Devathas — Shikhi (NE), Agni (SE), Pitra (SW), Roga (NW)</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Never place Puja Room in SE, SW, S, or W zones</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Never place Kitchen in NE or SW zones</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Never cut the NE corner of the plot — removes most auspicious zone</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Never place columns at Marma Sthana points</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Never use magnetic compass for direction — use GPS/satellite</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Never use the Sakkhi Chakra method — geometrically incorrect on rectangles</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Never place heavy construction in Brahma Sthana (centre)</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Never place Master Bedroom in NE — too much divine energy for sleep</li>
    <li style="margin-bottom:6px;">Never finalise plan without Ayadi calculation — Yoni must be auspicious</li>
  </ol>
</div>

